body:
Apple Inc. (AAPL) reported first quarter EPS of $3.36 after the bell Tuesday, up from $3.28 a year ago. Analysts expected EPS of $3.22. The stock is now up 4.18 on 7.2 million shares.

Apple traded in a range for the bulk of Tuesday's session and closed down by 0.28 at $121.35. The stock has been pulling back from the highs of the year for the past 2 days.
title: Apple Inc. (AAPL) Is Climbing On Stronger Than Expected Q1 Earnings
